column4: Ladbrokes "Free Bet At Ayr" Fillies' Nursery Handicap
column20: 5/2 Magic Box, 3/1 Radiance, 9/2 Magistery, 5/1 Aspiral, 11/2 Pretty Danielle, 12/1 Bearin Up, 20/1 Paroda Diva
column36: Impressive on debut; underwhelming since but retains potential now tackling a nursery
column37: 150,000gns breeze-up buy who impressed on debut at Yarmouth (7f, good) in July; underwhelming favourite in Salisbury novice (1m, good to firm) since but may have been feeling the ground (hung left); her very useful half-brother Nautical Force won on soft ground; has Group-race entries and retains potential for trainer who won this last year; possible player on nursery debut.

column4: Ladbrokes "Free Bet At Ayr" Fillies' Nursery Handicap
column20: 5/2 Magic Box, 3/1 Radiance, 9/2 Magistery, 5/1 Aspiral, 11/2 Pretty Danielle, 12/1 Bearin Up, 20/1 Paroda Diva
column32: D J Mackay & West Shaw Farm
column36: Carlisle maiden winner; begins handicap life on a fair mark and could continue to improve
column37: Built upon the promise of her debut second (5f, good) to win at Carlisle in July (7f, good to soft), and she was third of five in a valuable novice at Goodwood (1m, good to firm) last time; begins handicap life on a fair mark and could continue to improve for her top northern trainer.

column4: Ladbrokes "Free Bet At Ayr" Fillies' Nursery Handicap
column20: 5/2 Magic Box, 3/1 Radiance, 9/2 Magistery, 5/1 Aspiral, 11/2 Pretty Danielle, 12/1 Bearin Up, 20/1 Paroda Diva
column36: Two wins from her three nursery starts and could take latest 7lb rise in her stride
column37: Two wins from her three nursery starts, the latest at Catterick (7f, soft) in July when coming clear with one who has franked the form since; did it cosily last time and could take a 7lb rise in her stride.

column4: Ladbrokes "Free Bet At Ayr" Fillies' Nursery Handicap
column20: 5/2 Magic Box, 3/1 Radiance, 9/2 Magistery, 5/1 Aspiral, 11/2 Pretty Danielle, 12/1 Bearin Up, 20/1 Paroda Diva
column36: Kept on well for 6f nursery win at Carlisle recently and respected under 6lb penalty
column37: Returned to form to make all by half a length at Carlisle (6f, soft) ten days ago on her second nursery start, beating one who has posted wins either side; kept on well on that occasion and her dam was a 7f winner, both of which bode well for this step up in trip; respected under 6lb penalty.

column4: Ladbrokes "Free Bet At Ayr" Fillies' Nursery Handicap
column20: 5/2 Magic Box, 3/1 Radiance, 9/2 Magistery, 5/1 Aspiral, 11/2 Pretty Danielle, 12/1 Bearin Up, 20/1 Paroda Diva
column36: Kept on well for 3rd in 7f AW novice; today's ground will provide stiffer test of stamina
column37: Has made the frame in novice/maiden races on her last three starts, most recently keeping on well for third when upped to 7f at Lingfield (AW); today's slow ground will provide a stiffer test of stamina and that may well be to her liking; not ruled out on nursery debut.

column4: Ladbrokes "Free Bet At Ayr" Fillies' Nursery Handicap
column20: 5/2 Magic Box, 3/1 Radiance, 9/2 Magistery, 5/1 Aspiral, 11/2 Pretty Danielle, 12/1 Bearin Up, 20/1 Paroda Diva
column32: Mps Racing Ltd, Roger Thompson & Partner
column36: Went close in Kempton nursery in July but three lesser runs have followed
column37: Won Lingfield maiden (7f, good) in May and went close in Kempton nursery (7f, AW) in July; however, three lesser runs have followed.

column4: Ladbrokes "Free Bet At Ayr" Fillies' Nursery Handicap
column20: 5/2 Magic Box, 3/1 Radiance, 9/2 Magistery, 5/1 Aspiral, 11/2 Pretty Danielle, 12/1 Bearin Up, 20/1 Paroda Diva
column36: Third in two maidens last month but down the field at 18-1 on last week's nursery debut
column37: Third at Beverley (5f, good to firm) last month on second start then filled the same position at Ripon (6f, good); however, she was down the field on her nursery debut at Doncaster (6.5f, good to soft; 18-1) last Thursday.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Well-beaten sixth in Listed/Group 2 races but impressive in soft-ground novice previously
column37: Won on debut at Nottingham (6f, good) in June then easily made all in Carlisle novice (6f, soft); well-beaten sixth in Listed/Group 2 races on next two starts (7f/6f, good/good to firm) and needs to get back on track, but the slow ground could be a positive in view of his impressive Carlisle win.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Has made the frame in Listed races and could make an impact on nursery debut
column37: Won by 6l at Windsor (6f, good to firm) in June on second start and has made the frame in 6f Listed races at Newbury and Ripon on his last two starts; could make an impact on nursery debut if coping with the slow ground.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Disappointing favourite on nursery debut at York but trainer has excellent record in this
column37: Disappointing favourite on nursery debut at York but he'd shown considerable promise previously and is well worth a second look given that his trainer has won three of the last five runnings; unraced on slow ground.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Won Glorious Goodwood nursery then third in sales race at York; he's one to consider
column37: Made it 3-7 when suited by the step up to 6f and winning on nursery debut at Glorious Goodwood (good to soft; unraced on softer), and another big run when third of 21 in a sales race at York (6f, good to firm) last month; there could still be mileage in his mark and he's one to consider.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Has won in good style on last two starts and he's firmly in calculations on nursery debut
column37: Built upon the promise of his debut fourth (6f, good) to win over this C&D (good) last month, and he followed up in a novice at Redcar (6f, good to firm); he's done it in good style on those last two starts and his pedigree suggests slow ground will suit; firmly in calculations on nursery debut.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Off since finishing last at Royal Ascot but may nevertheless have potential off this mark
column37: Won at Ripon (5f, good) in June on third run then finished last when 66-1 at Royal Ascot; absent since and unraced on slow ground and beyond 5f, but has shown enough to hint he may have potential off this opening mark.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Won Hamilton maiden this month and he could continue to progress; up 6lb
column37: Won Hamilton maiden (6f, good to soft) last month on fourth start and returned to form when back on slow ground in a nursery at Hamilton (6f, good to soft) this month, prevailing by just over 1l; could continue to progress and he's a possible player up 6lb for last time.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Won Ffos Las nursery last month but failed to make an impact at Doncaster last week
column37: Newmarket trainer won this last year; short-headed at Windsor (6f, good) in July on second nursery start then went one better at Ffos Las (6f, good to soft); however, he failed to make an impact at Doncaster (6f, good) only last Friday and has to leave that run behind.

column4: Get Home Safe With Thistle Cabs EBF Nursery Handicap
column20: 4/1 Utmost Respect, 5/1 Ardisia, 11/2 Reciprocated,  Bye Law, 13/2 Amorim,  Go Vince Go, 9/1 Born Slippy, 12/1 Star Material,  Ubetterseethis
column36: Some good nursery form at Chester but exposed and probably vulnerable now back up in grade
column37: Off the mark at the sixth attempt on nursery debut at Chester (7f, good to firm) last month, and after finishing down the field at York he was a close third of six at Chester (7f, good) this month; however, this exposed colt is probably vulnerable now back up in grade; unraced on slow ground.

column37: Displayed improved form when runner-up at 66-1 in sales race at York (6f, good to firm) last month then easily got off the mark at the sixth attempt in a recent maiden at Hamilton (5f, good to soft); could be involved.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Has gone close in his two nurseries but has something to find now up in grade
column37: Pontefract maiden winner who went close last month in his first two nurseries (6f/5f), on the first occasion in a competitive race at York's Ebor meeting; however, he has something to find now up in grade.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Thirsk maiden winner; had an excuse at York but others have more substance to their claims
column37: The form of his maiden win at Thirsk last month has worked out well (5f, good to firm) and he raced away from the main action when mid-division in sales race at York (6f, good to firm) last time; however, others have more substance to their claims; below best on good to soft ground in July.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: 5f Listed winner who was outstayed when fifth in 6f Group 3 at the Curragh last time
column37: Made it 2-4 with Listed win at the Curragh (5f, good) last month, for which she carries a 3lb penalty today; outstayed when fifth in 6f Group 3 at the Curragh (good to yielding) last time; key player now back at 5f.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Won Musselburgh nursery last Saturday but very much up against it upped markedly in grade
column37: Won Beverley maiden (5f, good to firm) last month on seventh start and added a nursery win at Musselburgh (5f, good to soft) last Saturday; however, she looks very much up against it now upped markedly in grade.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Close Listed fifth at Newbury last month and might not be far away for bang-in-form yard
column37: Made it 2-3 when winning Thirsk novice (5f, good to firm) last month before close Listed fifth at Newbury (5f, good) seven days later, when she made the running; unraced on slow ground; her trainer is in tremendous form and she might not be far away.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Something to find today but she's been progressive in nurseries and is not ruled out
column37: Has improved for this tongue-tie, making it two wins in a row when making all on nursery debut at Ripon (5f, good to firm) before close second to Temple Of Athena in Chester nursery (5f, good to soft) last Saturday; something to find today but she had to work hard to lead from a wide stall at Chester and is now 2lb better off with the winner; progressive and not ruled out.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Made it 2-4 when winning nursery at Sandown; not discounted now back up in grade
column37: Won on debut at Windsor (6f, good to firm) in June and was back on song when winning a nursery at Sandown (5f, soft) three weeks ago; further improvement needed now back up in grade but that's possible; not discounted.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column32: Mrs J Woods R P Gallagher & Partner
column36: Fifth at York last time in a much hotter Listed race than this; could be thereabouts
column37: Close Listed fourth at Newbury last month (5f, good); beaten further when Listed fifth at York (5f, good to firm) eight days later but that form was strongly boosted in the Flying Childers; this will take less winning and she could be thereabouts for last year's winning yard; unraced on slow ground.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Only seventh in the Lowther but the drop back in grade can help, as might the return to 5f
column37: Impressive on debut at Beverley (5f, good to firm) in July and runner-up in Ripon novice (6f, good) next time, before finishing seventh in the Group 2 Lowther at York (6f, good to firm); improvement is needed but the drop back in grade can help, as might the return to 5f; not discounted.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Yet to win from 5 attempts but she's been running well in classy company; leading claims
column37: Yet to win from five attempts but she's been running well in some classy company, most recently third in a Group 3 at Longchamp (5f, very soft); leading claims in first-time cheekpieces.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Last in the Nunthorpe but strong form previously and could play a major role
column37: Beat subsequent Listed/Group 2 winner Revival Power to win valuable fillies' conditions race at Goodwood (5f, good) in July, then faced tough task against hardened sprinters when last in the Group 1 Nunthorpe; could bounce back and play a major role now back against 2yos; unraced on slow ground.

column4: British EBF Stallions Harry Rosebery Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 100/30 Shine On Me, 9/2 Ipanema Queen, 6/1 Lebron Power, 13/2 Daneh Of Dandy, 7/1 Our Cody, 8/1 Boston Dan, 10/1 Hanney Girl, 12/1 Temple Of Athena, 14/1 Pearl Fortune, 20/1 Chairmanfourtimes,  Rikki Tiki Tavi, 50/1 Arduis Invicta
column36: Others have stronger form but she's 2-2 on slow ground; could be in with an each-way shout
column37: Won on debut at Beverley (5f, soft) in June and returned to winning ways in nursery at Chester (5f, good to soft) last Saturday, which was her fifth start; others have stronger form but she's 2-2 on slow ground and could be in with an each-way shout.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Well beaten in May on sole run this year but 2-2 here (both Listed); key player if at best
column37: Well beaten at Newmarket in May on sole run this year but she's 2-2 here, both in 5f Listed races (good to firm/good to soft) and the latest last June; key player if back to her best following another break.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Below best in light campaign this term but in the mix on last autumn's soft-ground form
column37: Not at the top of her game in a light campaign this season but she's back on a slow surface today and is in the mix judged on the form of her two soft-ground handicap wins last autumn; interesting contender.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Made all in this last year and encouraging Listed third recently on belated reappearance
column37: Made all in this last year (good) and encouraging Listed third at Beverley (5f, good to firm) three weeks ago on her belated reappearance; won on soft ground at the start of her career; her usual visor returns (left off last time) and she has leading claims if building on her comeback run.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Irish raider who has been progressive in handicaps but improvement is needed today
column37: Progressive this year with two handicap wins, the latest at Chester (5f, good to soft) last month; has travelled from Ireland but she was well beaten in a Listed race at Tipperary last time and plenty of improvement is needed in first-time blinkers (replacing a visor).

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Running well in defeat in handicaps this term but soundly beaten in Listed race last month
column37: French soft-ground 2yo winner who has been running well in defeat in handicaps this season; however, she needs something extra on that form to come out on top today and was soundly beaten in a Listed race last month.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: 3yo with 6 wins this year; today's company demands another step forward, but it's possible
column37: Highly progressive 3yo front-runner who made it six wins for the year (including one here) when scoring at York (5.4f, good) in July; has continued in good form on her next two starts; unproven on slow ground and today's company demands another step forward, but that's possible.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Lightly raced 3yo who showed improvement when Listed runner-up at 16-1 at Pontefract
column37: Lightly raced 3yo who showed improved form when a Listed runner-up at 16-1 at Pontefract (6f, good to firm) last month, and the winner followed up in a French Group 3; the return to slow ground poses a question but she's of interest following that latest performance; cheekpieces go on.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Solid 5f handicap form this term; something to find but the extra yardage could be a plus
column37: 3yo who has shown some solid 5f handicap form this season and kept on strongly for sixth of 19 behind Star Of Mehmas in a handicap at York (5f, good to firm) last month; has something to find now up in grade but the extra yardage could be a plus; effective on soft ground; each-way possible.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Listed fourth at Pontefract last month but she's down the pecking order today
column37: Won Salisbury novice (6f, good to firm) last month before Listed fourth at Pontefract (6f, good to firm) four days later, wearing a hood each time; similar form when sixth in handicap at Yarmouth (6f, good to soft) on Tuesday; however, she's down the pecking order today; the hood returns.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: 2yo Listed win here 12 months ago; defied top weight in York h'cap latest; strong claims
column37: Won the Listed 2yo event on this card 12 months ago (5f, good) and posted a last-gasp win off top weight in a competitive handicap at York (5f, good to firm) last month; today's trip could be a good fit and she's a strong candidate if handling the ground (unraced on a slow surface).

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
column20: 7/2 Beautiful Diamond, 4/1 Star Of Mehmas, 11/2 Star Of Lady M, 8/1 Stormy Impact, 9/1 Magic Basma, 10/1 Luna A Inbhir Nis, 12/1 Sophia's Starlight, 14/1 Nad Alshiba Green,  Tiva, 16/1 Rhyme Dust, 20/1 Lady Of Andros,  Stella Alpina, 25/1 Billie Be Quick
column36: Irish raider but only sixth in Listed race at Tipperary last time; improvement is needed
column37: Won Tipperary maiden (5f, good) last month on eighth start and has travelled from Ireland for today's run; however, she was only sixth in a Listed race at Tipperary (5f, yielding) last time and improvement is needed.

column4: Arran Scottish Sprint EBF Fillies' Stakes (Listed Race)
